The business entity surviving from the merger shall deliver to the Secretary of State for filing articles of merger duly executed by each constituent business entity setting forth:
The name and jurisdiction of formation or organization of each constituent business entity which is to merge;
The name of the surviving business entity;
The information required by KRS 275.355(2)(d);
Any amendment to the articles of organization of the surviving limited liability company;
A statement that the plan of merger was duly authorized and approved by each constituent business entity in accordance with KRS 275.350; and
If the surviving entity is not a business entity organized under the laws of this Commonwealth, a statement that the surviving business entity:
Agrees that it may be served with process in this Commonwealth in any proceeding for enforcement of any obligation of any constituent business entity party to the merger that was organized under the laws of this Commonwealth, as well as for enforcement of any obligation of the surviving business entity arising from the merger; and
Appoints the Secretary of State as its agent for service of process in any such proceeding. The surviving entity shall specify the address to which a copy of the process shall be mailed to it by the Secretary of State.
